Sentence: The exact critical temperature for a-Mo 2 C, b-Mo 2 C, g-MoC 1-x and a-W 2 C was later reported by Morton et al. to be 6-7.3 K, 5.1-7.2 K, 7.4-8.9 K, and 2.95-3.05 K, respectively.

The superconductivity of TMCs, including NbC, ZrC, HfC, TaC, a-WC, a-Mo 2 C and a-W 2 C, has long been investigated by Clinard and co-workers 12 in the temperature range from 2 to 300 K, and all of them show a superconducting transition near 10 K.
